  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine if sleep deprivation results in increased
      esophageal acid exposure in healthy controls and gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)
      patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      To determine if increased esophageal acid exposure is mediated by altering appetite
      regulation. To assess if there is any relationship between sleep deprivation and the serum
      level of TNF-alfa (a protein that can be elevated in inflammation).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
